    "created_at": "2015-10-29T17:32:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-29T17:41:40Z",
    "body": "After more investigation, it seems that the \"blur\" event on Ubuntu and Windows is not being fired IF the \"always-on-top\" option is set to True. But this is not the behavior on OS X. \n\nHowever, if the window is always on top, doesn't mean it is always in focus, so a blur event should be fired when the window goes out of focus.\n\nSetting the window to always-on-top using setAlwaysOnTop(true) doesn't break the blur event.\n"
  },
